And what was your job, Sherbert? I went in and 
established the layout of the camp and stayed in

33:37.816 --> 33:44.926
there until they got the things set up, and then I 
came on back. And then I went in and did the same

33:44.946 --> 33:48.170
thing. Somebody else was in charge of that. And 
then I did the same thing, and when they liberated

33:49.832 --> 33:56.121
Paris, I went in I made the assessment on what we had 
to do to Le Bourget. Le Bourget is where Lindbergh

34:00.002 --> 34:05.310
landed and had just been bombed to hell. They told 
us that we were going to have to operate out of Le

34:05.650 --> 34:18.970
Bourget because the inner theater aircraft, the 
big transports, were going to work from Orly to the

34:05.650 --> 34:18.970
other airports.

