This same lieutenant

44:30.777 --> 44:41.151
named Carter from Boston, Massachusetts, he was a 
subordinate of mine and was a provost marshal. And

44:41.171 --> 44:46.939
he was out one day and he found a marshaling yard 
that had a huge supply of coal. And it was the size of

44:52.149 --> 45:00.898
coal that you would use in a boiler, like on a 
locomotive or even in a heating plant. And he came

45:00.918 --> 45:02.980
back and reported it to me. And I immediately told 
the old man about it. And he called the chief of

45:05.663 --> 45:07.865
staff in. And the chief of staff was Colonel Henry 
Bevelle. And he said, OK, Henry. you'll take half

